    "created_at": "2021-03-03T00:03:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2021-03-03T00:03:08Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "To go into more detail here -- before 0.4.9, all contracts would be placed under the `''` source path in the `contracts` output.  This means we can't find its corresponding source in the usual way.  Instead, we'd have to get the source index from the [constructor] source map, then find the corresponding source by finding the one with the appropriate index.\r\n\r\nNote this would only work back to 0.3.6, since before that there are no source maps.\r\n\r\nAlso worth noting, not that we have any intent of doing this, but before 0.1.6, the Solidity compiler could only compile one file at a time, so we'd have to do a separate invocation for each file if we wanted to support that, but I'm pretty sure that's not happening.",
